\section{Account Types}{

KuCoin uses separate accounts for different purposes:
\itemize{
\item \code{"MAIN"}: Funding account — deposits land here by default.
\item \code{"TRADE"}: Spot trading account — required for HF orders.
\item \code{"MARGIN"}: Cross-margin account.
\item \code{"ISOLATED"}: Isolated-margin account (requires \code{fromAccountTag}/\code{toAccountTag} for symbol).
\item \code{"CONTRACT"}: Futures account.
}
}

\section{Transfer Types}{

\itemize{
\item \code{"INTERNAL"}: Between your own accounts (e.g., MAIN → TRADE).
\item \code{"PARENT_TO_SUB"}: From master to sub-account.
\item \code{"SUB_TO_PARENT"}: From sub-account to master.
}
}

