\subsection{Method \code{add_transfer()}}{
Add Transfer (Universal)

Transfers funds between account types within your own KuCoin account, or
between master and sub-accounts. This is essential for trading bots because
deposits land in the \strong{main} account, but HF spot orders require funds in
the \strong{trade} account.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Build Body}: Constructs JSON body with required transfer parameters.
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated POST to the universal transfer endpoint.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Returns \code{data.table} with the transfer order ID.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{POST https://api.kucoin.com/api/v3/accounts/universal-transfer}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/account-info/transfer/flex-transfer}{KuCoin Flex Transfer}

Verified: 2026-05-23
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Bot Startup}: Transfer deposited funds from MAIN to TRADE before placing orders.
\item \strong{Profit Harvesting}: Move profits from TRADE to MAIN before withdrawing.
\item \strong{Sub-Account Funding}: Distribute funds to sub-accounts running independent strategies.
\item \strong{Idempotency}: Use \code{clientOid} (UUID) to prevent duplicate transfers on retry.
}
}

